peg&quot;,&quot;srcNoWatermark&quot;:null,&quot;fullscreen&quot;:null,&quot;imageSize&quot;:null,&quot;height&quot;:1024,&quot;width&quot;:1024,&quot;resizeWidth&quot;:710,&quot;bytes&quot;:68662,&quot;alt&quot;:null,&quot;title&quot;:null,&quot;type&quot;:&quot;image/jpeg&quot;,&quot;href&quot;:null,&quot;belowTheFold&quot;:false,&quot;topImage&quot;:true,&quot;internalRedirect&quot;:null}" class="sizing-normal" alt="" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Ffe795b6d-eaa0-4806-8eb9-cd5afcdf2443_1024x1024.jpeg 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Ffe795b6d-eaa0-4806-8eb9-cd5afcdf2443_1024x1024.jpeg 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Ffe795b6d-eaa0-4806-8eb9-cd5afcdf2443_1024x1024.jpeg 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Ffe795b6d-eaa0-4806-8eb9-cd5afcdf2443_1024x1024.jpeg 1456w" sizes="100vw" fetchpriority="high"></picture></div></a> <polyline points="15 3 21 3 21 9"></polyline><polyline points="9 21 3 21 3 15"></polyline><line x1="21" x2="14" y1="3" y2="10"></line><line x1="3" x2="10" y1="21" y2="14"></line><figcaption class="image-caption"> GPT-4 的艺术作品。提示：“互联网之死”</figcaption></figure></div><p>我们所知道的互联网已经消亡过一次了。 2010 年代，智能手机和大众社交媒体（Twitter/Facebook/Instagram）的兴起引发了互联网资深人士所说的整个互联网的<a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Eternal_September">“永恒九月</a>事件”。 “永恒的九月”是一个古老的俚语，指的是一群普通人涌入以前舒适的精品在线空间。当普通人拥有一台高速袖珍电脑，将他们 24/7 与社交媒体世界连接起来时，互联网就不再是怪人和业余爱好者的领域，而是成为我们整个社会的城镇广场。</p><p>在我看来，这并不是一个很大的改变。人类并没有进化到所有人都在同一个房间里。早期的互联网是一个非常特殊的时代，当时网络世界主要作为那些不太融入线下世界的人的临时逃避或释放阀；大众社交媒体<a href="https://bfi.uchicago.edu/insight/research-summary/when-product-markets-become-collective-traps-the-case-of-social-media/">将互联网变成了一个集体陷阱</a>，一个你<em>必须</em>去的地方，而不是一个你可以逃走的地方。如果你看一下美国青少年的幸福感图表，你会发现从 90 年代中期到 2000 年代，情况有所好转，然后又急剧恶化： </p><div class="captioned-image-container"><figure><a class="image-link is-viewable-img image2" target="_blank" href="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fdd6e1312-42b2-444b-b036-0c952ae2ebbd_990x495.jpeg" data-component-name="Image2ToDOM"><div class="image2-inset"><picture><source type="image/webp" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fdd6e1312-42b2-444b-b036-0c952ae2ebbd_990x495.jpeg 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fdd6e1312-42b2-444b-b036-0c952ae2ebbd_990x495.jpeg 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fdd6e1312-42b2-444b-b036-0c952ae2ebbd_990x495.jpeg 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fdd6e1312-42b2-444b-b036-0c952ae2ebbd_990x495.jpeg 1456w" sizes="100vw"><img src="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fdd6e1312-42b2-444b-b036-0c952ae2ebbd_990x495.jpeg" width="990" height="495" data-attrs="{&quot;src&quot;:&quot;https://substack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com/public/images/dd6e1312-42b2-444b-b036-0c952ae2ebbd_990x495.jpeg&quot;,&quot;srcNoWatermark&quot;:null,&quot;fullscreen&quot;: