dia.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F8ad96b5d-35b0-44f3-8a15-6b9e7caca15d_951x623.jpeg 1456w" sizes="100vw" loading="lazy"></picture><div class="image-link-expand"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="lucide lucide-maximize2 "><polyline points="15 3 21 3 21 9"></polyline><polyline points="9 21 3 21 3 15"></polyline><line x1="21" x2="14" y1="3" y2="10"></line><line x1="3" x2="10" y1="21" y2="14"></line></svg></div></div><figcaption class="image-caption">资料来源： <a href="https://scholar.harvard.edu/files/jorgenson/files/industryoriginsus_japanproductivitygap_economicsystemsresearch.pdf">Jorgenson &amp; Nomura (2007)</a></figcaption></figure></div><p>当他们按行业进行细分时，他们发现，尽管日本确实在某些行业击败了美国，但这种领先地位有时会随着时间的推移而逆转： </p><div class="captioned-image-container"><figure><a class="image-link is-viewable-img image2" target="_blank" href="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F6c8de91e-fcfa-4385-8924-deabaaad494c_688x747.jpeg" data-component-name="Image2ToDOM"><div class="image2-inset"><picture><source type="image/webp" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F6c8de91e-fcfa-4385-8924-deabaaad494c_688x747.jpeg 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F6c8de91e-fcfa-4385-8924-deabaaad494c_688x747.jpeg 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F6c8de91e-fcfa-4385-8924-deabaaad494c_688x747.jpeg 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_webp,q_aut